We, therefore, recommended that the LCE:
1. Immediately create the Inventory Committee, composed of an adequate number of members, and complete the physical count in three (3) months or less and submit a report thereon. The Inventory Committee shall have at least one member each from the Accounting and Property Divisions/Units of the agency;
2. Instruct the Inventory Committee to plan/strategize on how to conduct and complete the physical inventory within the prescribed period by preparing a PIP duly approved by the Mayor, containing the specific assignments/duties of the Committee members, the cut-off date, and a schedule specifying the dates and locations of the inventory taking activities from start-up to the targeted completion of physical inventory;
3. Thereafter, the Inventory Committee shall submit the approved PIP to the Audit Team at least ten (10) calendar days before the scheduled start of inventory; and
4. Instruct the GSO to update the property records based on the result of the physical count and reconcile the same with the accounting records to come up with correct balances of PPE accounts.

Municipal Mayor direct the concerned Municipal Officers:
5. Municipal Engineer – Provide the local accountant and the GSO with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects and the water supply system;
6. GSO – Keep a complete PC to all the infrastructure assets and maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map;
7. Municipal Accountant – Prepare the JV to record the beginning balance of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card;
8. Support the JV with the Registry of Public Infrastructures on the corresponding accounts of the Local Road Network and the Water Supply System. Work on the distribution of cost for road components and the water supply system and determine the corresponding depreciated replacement cost for road components with no available cost per registry;
9. Keep and maintain subsidiary records of roads and road components and the water supply system;
10. Prepare a lapsing schedule for the computation of the depreciation for each infrastructure account at the end of the year.

23. Must made sure that the conditions and requirements prescribed in Appendix I of RA 9184 are duly complied with prior to the implementation/construction of any project to be undertaken by administration;
