25. Install safety and security measures so that the life and property of any prospective contractors can properly be safeguarded.

21. We recommended that management initiate measures designed to come up with a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) with the GSIS defining therein the agreed balance of payables to GSIS, if any, and the terms and conditions in the settlement thereof. The following steps may help in facilitating reconciliation of records:
a.) Secure detailed profile of the payables per GSIS records;
b.) Reconstruct old GSIS accounts, if necessary, and update records;
c.) Reconstruct old personnel profile, if necessary, and update personnel profile;
d.) Counter-check GSIS records with the reconstructed and updated accounting and personnel records of the LGU;
e.) Negotiate with the GSIS for any differences that may be noted during counter-checking activity;
f.) Enter into a formal agreement with the GSIS in the form of a Memorandum of Agreement (MOA); and
g.) Appropriate fund for the settlement of any payables to the GSIS as agreed in the MOA.

